Two cyclists have died following a collision with a car in Barnsley, South Yorkshire. Emergency services rushed to Royston Road in Cudworth at 9.07pm last night after the alarm was raised. Police had received reports of a crash between a car and two cyclists. Upon arrival, both the cyclists were pronounced dead at the scene. Officers are now working to formally identify them. The car involved in the crash, believed to be a red Volkswagen Golf, failed to stop at the scene. It was later found abandoned in Bleak Avenue, Shafton. Bleak Avenue is less than a five-minute drive from where the crash took place on Royston Road. A 37-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving. In a statement, South Yorkshire Police said: ‘Officers are working tracing another man in connection with the incident. ‘We are appealing for anyone who witnessed the incident or who was driving in the area at the time and may have seen the Volkswagen Golf or cyclists to get in touch. ‘We are particularly keen to hear from those with dash-cam footage. ‘You can pass information to police via our new online live chat, our online portal or by calling 101. Please quote incident number 1089 of 20 January when you get in touch.’ You can access the South Yorkshire Police online portal here: www.southyorks.police.uk/contact-us/report-something Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.